Azure Functions are a core part of serverless computing, where infrastructure management is abstracted away.

Developers focus only on writing code while Azure handles scaling and execution.

For example, a function automatically scales during high traffic and scales down when idle.

A real-life use case is event-driven systems like processing messages from queues or handling API requests.

Another example is automation tasks such as scheduled backups.

Serverless computing improves efficiency, reduces costs, and accelerates development.
